Source: pg-oidc-validator
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), cargo, clang, libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.7.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/UnAfraid/pg_oidc_validator_rust

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-oidc-validator
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-oidc-validator
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: OIDC bearer-token validator for PostgreSQL 18
 pg_oidc_validator validates PostgreSQL 18 OAuth bearer tokens through OIDC
 discovery and the issuer JWKS endpoint, then returns the token subject as the
 authenticated identity. Load it with oauth_validator_libraries.
